There is a case when {{mongoc_gridfs_file_readv()}} returns -1 (failure), but the subsequent call to {{mongoc_gridfs_file_error()}} returns {{false}} indicating that there is no actual error.

This seems to contradict with what the manual states about [mongoc_gridfs_file_readv()|http://mongoc.org/libmongoc/current/mongoc_gridfs_file_readv.html]:

bq. Returns the number of bytes read, or -1 on failure. Use mongoc_gridfs_file_error to retrieve error details.

Interestingly, but for [mongoc_gridfs_file_writev()|http://mongoc.org/libmongoc/current/mongoc_gridfs_file_writev.html], it states that {{errno}} will be set:

bq. Returns the number of bytes written or -1 upon error and errno is set.

Not sure how potential database failures will be propagated via {{errno}}, but at least I can't blame this one for now albeit it looks a bit inconsistent.

Please see the example below.

