h4. Summary

The "$db" sent to mongocryptd is always "admin": [https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-c-driver/blob/b759748551320ffa1105dcb5724970bfdac94fd6/src/libmongoc/src/mongoc/mongoc-crypt.c#L311.|https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-c-driver/blob/b759748551320ffa1105dcb5724970bfdac94fd6/src/libmongoc/src/mongoc/mongoc-crypt.c#L311]

This is an error on mongocryptd 6.0.0-rc6 and newer when the command includes "encryptionInformation"
h4. Background

mongocryptd 6.0.0-rc5 responds with an error if the database name in "encryptionInformation" does not match "$db". Example:
{code}{
    "find": "default",
    "filter": {},
    "encryptionInformation": {
        "type": 1,
        "schema": {
            "default.default": {
                "escCollection": "enxcol_.default.esc",
                "eccCollection": "enxcol_.default.ecc",
                "ecocCollection": "enxcol_.default.ecoc",
                "fields": []
            }
        }
    },
    "$db": "admin"
}
{code}
mongocryptd 6.0.0-rc5 and newer will respond with:
{code}{
    "ok": 0.0,
    "errmsg": "Namespace in encryptionInformation: 'default.default' does not match namespace given in command: 'admin.default'",
    "code": 6411900,
    "codeName": "Location6411900"
}
{code}

In https://mongoc.org/libmongoc/current/mongoc_database_find_collections_with_opts.html

{code}
   if (mongoc_cursor_error (cursor, &error))
      fprintf (stderr, "%s\n", error.msg);
   }
{code}

Produces

{code}
main.c:139:37: error: 'bson_error_t' {aka 'struct _bson_error_t'} has no member named 'msg'
  139 |       fprintf (stderr, "%s\n", error.msg);
      |                                     ^
{code}

Looking at definition in source, the field is called message:

{code}
typedef struct _bson_error_t {
   uint32_t domain;
   uint32_t code;
   char message[BSON_ERROR_BUFFER_SIZE];
} bson_error_t BSON_ALIGNED_END (8);
{code}

h4. Summary

Building the CDriver on a M1 macOS fails because of a call to an undeclared function (getpagesize). However, this function is available on macOS M1. Using the configuration and the build commands listed below, the c driver can't be built.
h4. Environment

C driver version is 1.23.0

The host is on MacOS Monterey 12.6 on the M1 chip ARM64. 

clang version 15.0.2
h4. How to Reproduce

These steps were taken from the C Driver Getting Started guide.

Configure cmake:
{code:java}
cmake \    
-DCMAKE_C_COMPILER="<path to LLVM>/bin/clang" \    
-DENABLE_MAINTAINER_FLAGS=ON \    
-DMONGO_SANITIZE="address;leak" \    
-B./cmake-build {code}
Then build the executables:
{code:java}
cmake --build cmake-build --target example-client {code}
Then run the executable 
{code:java}
./cmake-build/src/libmongoc/example-client {code}
This error will appear in 
